        img {
            display: block;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 id="heading1" class="text-center"><b>Stool specimen</b></h1>

    <h3>Follow this procedure for stool specimen collection</h3>

    <p>
        Obtain unformed stool specimens.
    </p>
   
    <p>
        Take parts of the stool that look bloody or slimy (contain mucous/pus).
    </p>


    <p>
        Fill each container at least 1/3 full.
    </p>

    

    <p>
        Replace the lid.
    </p>

    <p>
        Complete the N1 PHC request form. Please provide the suspected clinical diagnosis to
        enhance appropriate processing of the specimen in the laboratory.
    </p>

    <p>
        Do not submit more than one stool specimen for any individual patient within a 24 hour
        period.
    </p>

    <p>
        Stool specimens can be collected at any time of day and can be stored at room
        temperature for up to 24hr. Where room temperature exceed 25°C then store in a
        refrigerator (2-5°C).
    </p>


</body>
</html>